<sect1 id="winetricks" xreflabel="Winetricks-&winetricks-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="winetricks.html"?>

  <title>Winetricks-&winetricks-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="winetricks">
    <primary sortas="a-winetricks">Winetricks</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to Winetricks</title>

    <para>
      Winetricks is a shell script that can fix various issues with <ulink
      url="&glfs-website;/wine/wine.html">Wine</ulink>. Most often, these
      issues arise from files being missing that some applications may expect,
      such as font files. This package can download those files, and extract
      them if needed.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download: <ulink url="&winetricks-download;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Winetricks Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/basicnet/curl.html">cURL</ulink> or
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/basicnet/wget.html">Wget</ulink> and
      <ulink url="&glfs-website;/wine/wine.html">Wine</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/7zip.html">7zip</ulink>,
      &unzip;,
      <xref linkend="libmspack"/>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/unrar.html">UnRar</ulink>, and
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/xsoft/xdg-utils.html">xdg-utils</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Optional</bridgehead>
    <para role="optional">
      <ulink url="&arch-pkgs;/extra/x86_64/kdialog">kdialog</ulink> (for KDE)
      or
      <ulink url="&arch-pkgs;/extra/x86_64/zenity">zenity</ulink> (for GNOME);
      this package uses either to provide a GUI interface but is optional
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Winetricks</title>

    <para>
      Install Winetricks as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>
  
